the encyclopedia of esoteric teachings the book is amazing in its amount of topics covered , from gnostic beliefs , the lost city of atlantis , who really wrote shakespeare , who were the rosecrucians , secret meanings of the zodiac , alchemy , pythagorean math , mystery schools and much , much , much , more at 56 chapters . for an introduction to every esoteric religion in history , buy this book.i read it from cover to cover and it was enthralling for all 672 pages.also get `` lectures on ancient philosophy '' to go into more depth